Teenager Wins First Gold of China's Ethnic Games
Qing Ming, a 13-year-old Mongolian who grew up in the grazing area,
came away with the first gold of the games Wednesday in the event of
1,000 meter speed horse race, beating Miao nationality Wu Chengjiang
into second place.
Under the inspiration of the partisan crowd, Zhaxi Redan handed the
hosts its first gold at the 1,000 meter horse walk (its gait similar to
walk), followed by Tibetan Cai Bao from Qinghai province northwest of
China.
With 25 golds at stake, this national games of traditional ethnic
minority sports feature four competitive events including horse racing,
top whipping, yajia (similar to tug-of-war) and crossbow shooting.
